AB  - This paper derives and compares alternative formulations of price and output formation for the Mexican economy over the period 1961–1981. A structuralist type model with working capital is found to dominate its monetarist and keynesian counterparts. A breakdown of the causes of inflation is offered, and some simulations are carried out to highlight some trade-offs among real wages, the real exchange rate, real interest rates and output.
